# Frontend Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env.local to customize your configuration

# =========================================================================
# PROXY ARCHITECTURE (Default - Recommended)
# =========================================================================
# The application uses Vite's built-in proxy to route backend requests.
# This means:
# - Frontend: http://your-host:5173 (publicly accessible)
# - Backend: http://127.0.0.1:8000 (internal only, proxied through frontend)
# - API Docs: http://your-host:5173/docs (proxied to backend)
#
# Benefits: More secure, only one port to expose, no CORS issues
# No configuration needed - works automatically!

# =========================================================================
# EXTERNAL BACKEND OVERRIDE (Advanced Use Cases)
# =========================================================================
# Only set VITE_API_BASE_URL if you need to connect to an external backend
# Examples:
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://external-backend.com:8000
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://api.yourdomain.com

# For standard deployments, leave this unset to use the proxy

# =========================================================================
# DEPLOYMENT CONFIGURATION
# =========================================================================
# ALB Hostname (for AWS ALB deployments)
# Set this environment variable when deploying behind an Application Load Balancer
# Example:
# export ALB_HOSTNAME=your-alb-hostname.us-west-2.elb.amazonaws.com
# Then run: ./start_all.sh